<NewGameSettings>
  <!--EnemyRaceOptions: Define which race IDs are able to be turned on or off in advanced options
        EnemyRaceIDGroup: Group of race IDs which is used to create a check box
          Name: Text to display for check box
          RaceID: ID of race which is toggled with this check box.  Supports an arbitrary amount
  -->
  <!--Profession: Default profession. Starting gnomes with this profession will have higher starting skills in the allowed skills
        Name: Name of this profession
        Skill: Skills allowed for this profession
  -->
  <!--Settler:
        Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
        RaceID: ID of race
        Profession: Name of starting profession
        HeldItem: Item held in hand. Supports as many as can be carried
          Item: Weighted item to generate
            ItemID: ID of item to generate
            Weight (Optional): Default is 1. Weight that this item is selected over others in this group
          MaterialID (Optional): Default is random based on CoreItemIDsToMaterialIDs.  ID of material
  -->
  <!--FarmAnimal:
        Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
        RaceID: ID of race
        Gender: Gender.  Supports Male, Female, Neuter
  -->
  <!--ItemToGenerate: Supports an arbitrary amount
        Item: Weighted item to generate.  Supports arbitrary amount
          ItemID: ID of item to generate
          Weight (Optional): Default is 1. Weight that this item is selected over others in this group
        MaterialID (Optional): Default is random based on CoreItemIDsToMaterialIDs.  ID of material
        Quantity (Optional): Default is 1.  Quantity of item to generate
        Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
  -->
  <!--Container:
        Item: Weighted item to generate.  Supports arbitrary amount
          ItemID: ID of item to generate
          Weight (Optional): Default is 1. Weight that this item is selected over others in this group
        MaterialID (Optional): Default is random based on CoreItemIDsToMaterialIDs.  ID of material
        Quantity (Optional): Default is 1.  Quantity of item to generate
        Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
        Contents: Contents of this container.  Must be valid contents
          Item: Weighted item to generate.  Supports arbitrary amount
            ItemID: ID of item to generate
            Weight (Optional): Default is 1. Weight that this item is selected over others in this group
          MaterialID (Optional): Default is random based on CoreItemIDsToMaterialIDs.  ID of material
          Quantity (Optional): Default fills the container.  Quantity of item to generate
          Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
  -->
  <!--Pile: Supports an arbitrary amount
        Item: Weighted item to generate.  Supports arbitrary amount
          ItemID: ID of item to generate
          Weight (Optional): Default is 1. Weight that this item is selected over others in this group
        MaterialID (Optional): Default is random based on CoreItemIDsToMaterialIDs.  ID of material
        Quantity (Optional): Default fills the pile.  Quantity of item to generate
        Offset: Vector2 offset from start position
  -->
